<br>
TZ would be the first and easiest only having a ATK debuff and AE and only hitting at 800 a round with no flurry. Unslowable<br>
<br>
VZ would be a huge step up from TZ by hitting for 1100 and flurrying, AoE rampage, and a *proc* that has a -400 ATK debuff and 20% slow. More a resists fight as the AoE rampage could proc slow on your melees. Unslowable<br>
<br>
Then comes Rallos who hits quad/flurry 1250, AoE rampages, has close to a million hitpoints, huge regen, has a proc that will pretty much cripple your MT, and he's nonslowable. Also has a small MR based AE that is nearly irresistable that takes 300hp/200mana.<br>
<br>
Tallon Zek<br>
HP:400,000<br>
Flurry:No<br>
AoE Rampage:Yes(every 20 rounds)<br>
Quad:yes<br>
Max Hit:800<br>
AE:-300 ATK, 3-slot debuff<br>
Slowable:No<br>
Regen:1,000hp per tick<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
Vallon Zek<br>
HP:600,000<br>
Flurry:Yes<br>
AoE Rampage:Yes(every 15 rounds)<br>
Quad:yes<br>
Max Hit:1100<br>
Proc(on MT):-400 ATK, 20% slow<br>
Slowable:No<br>
Regen:2,500hp per tick<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
Rallos Zek<br>
HP:850,000<br>
Flurry:Yes<br>
AoE Rampage:Yes(every 10 rounds)<br>
Quad:yes<br>
Max Hit:1250<br>
Proc(on MT):-400AC, -500ATK, -50STA, 50hp/tick DoT<br>
AE: 300 DD+200 manadrain, MR based<br>
Slowable:No<br>
Regen:5,000hp per tick<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
